From MUNIZB RWTMS MUNIZB Subject Long Island was Why use AC at for SSF power on Date Fri Apr GMT Edmund Hack arabia hack writes In article Pat writes I always thought GD's Fighter plants were in Long No Northrup has a plant on Long I don't think Northrup ever had a plant on Long The two main airframe manufacturers there were Fairchild Republic which closed its doors after the T cancellation and Grumman which is still hanging on last I time I called I think Sperry also started If you're ever in the area check out the Cradle of Aviation Museum at Mitchell field now mostly parking lots behind the Nassau Coliseum and the community college Good display of vehicles from Long Island including a LEM flight Disclaimer Opinions stated are solely my own unless I change my mind Ben Muniz MUNIZB RWTMS w Space Station Freedom Rocketdyne Rockwell Structural Loads and Dynamics Man will not fly for fifty years Wilbur to Orville Wright